<p><b>Tias Mortigjija</b> (7 April 1913 — 14 September 1947) was a <a href="/wiki/Croats" title="Croats">Croatian</a> journalist, publicist, and member of the Croatian Historical Revolution, best known for his activities during the existence of the <a href="/wiki/Independent_State_of_Croatia" title="Independent State of Croatia">Independent State of Croatia</a>. During this period he was chief editor of the most important Croatian newspaper and magazine, <i><a href="/wiki/Spremnost_1942-1945" title="Spremnost 1942-1945" class="mw-redirect">Spremnost</a></i>.</p>
<p></p>
